```julia
abstract type AbstractVehicle end

function ispersonal(vehicle::AbstractVehicle)
    return @switch vehicle.type
        @case "Car"     return true
        @case "Motorcycle" return true
        @case "Bus"     return false
        @case "Truck"   return false
        @default      return false
end
```

This function uses a pattern matching macro `@switch` to check the type of the vehicle and returns a boolean indicating whether it is a personal vehicle or not. The macro `@switch` is part of the Julia standard library and allows for a compact syntax to handle different cases.
